        "goal_understanding": "The goal is to navigate a grid-based puzzle, using modifier tiles to change a carried piece's shape, color, and rotation so that it matches the requirements of goal cells, then step onto those goal cells to complete them. All goals in a level must be completed to advance, and the ultimate aim is to complete all levels.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "The game is turn-based, where each move in a cardinal direction consumes 1 stamina. Running out of stamina costs a life and resets stamina to maximum; losing all lives ends the game. Walls block movement and are reported as blocked_directions. Tiles include shape changers (cycle through 6 shapes), color changers (cycle orange\u2192blue\u2192green\u2192red\u2192orange), and rotation changers (rotate 90\u00b0 clockwise). Goal cells activate only when the carried piece's shape, color, and rotation exactly match the goal's requirements. The player must plan routes to conserve stamina, avoid blocked directions, and sequence modifier usage to satisfy goals."
